    </div></div><p>Harvest&#x27;s example demonstrates how to design edit functionality for multiple fields:</p><ul role="list"><li>Users select the project they want to modify.</li><li>An &quot;Edit Project&quot; button allows changes to any information.</li><li>For potentially problematic changes, a warning pop-up alerts users.</li></ul><p>This approach makes editing complex information easier and safer.</p><h2>Deleting</h2><p>Depending on what the user has to delete, screen designer has to come up with different user experience and ensure different level of security and avoid accidental mistakes. </p><h3>Figma – delete account</h3><div class="w-embed"><div class="wrap-slider-blog">
      <div class="swiper swiper-initialized swiper-horizontal swiper-backface-hidden">
        <div class="swiper-wrapper" id="swiper-wrapper-f7fd2a1d1039f73c3" aria-live="polite" style="transition-duration: 0ms; transform: translate3d(0px, 0px, 0px); transition-delay: 0ms;">
          <div class="swiper-slide swiper-slide-active" style="width: 700px;" role="group" aria-label="1 / 4"><img class="slider-blog-image" src="
